[The] merry boys of Christmas, or The milk-maids new-years-gift. When lads and lasses take delight, together for to be; they pass away the winter night, and live most merrily. To the tune of, Hey boys up go we.
1 sheet ([1] p.) : ill. (woodcuts)
s.n., [London : 1660?]
Place and date of publication from Wing CD-ROM, 1996. Verse: "Come, come my roaring ranting boys,". Imperfect: copy stained and cut; top and right side of sheet, including imprint, wanting. Reproduction of original in the British Library.
